channel.title: Java error when trying to select dat file in Tom's Cache Editor
channel.description:
Hi, I'm trying to edit my cache but when I load a dat file it will display the following below...
[URL=http://s1056.photobucket.com/user/BroskiMode/media/server_zps97qwrtjb.png.html][IMG]http://i1056.photobucket.com/albums/t377/BroskiMode/server_zps97qwrtjb.png[/img][/URL]
How do I get around this? Help.

item.title: Java error when trying to select dat file in Tom's Cache Editor
item.dc:creator: @Tree Tree
item.description:
@Tree wrote:

[quote=“WWWYKI, post:13, topic:553921”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=672843.msg4499441#msg4499441 date=1448344474]

Tried that still no luck. Still getting that exception error everywhere i go. I’ve seen a few people online with the same issue. I’ve tried using a default cache from the source but no difference

Like I said:
Tom’s cache editor was made for the original 317/377 cache that was in like the first clients released… Some people modified it to have no limits, but this changes nothing for the data it’s reading.
If you pack 667 data into your cache, the cache editor isn’t made to read it. Therefore it will give an error.
You understand?
[/quote]

Ah I see. At least I know now. Thanks for trying.[/quote]

No problem.
